modelIdentification.name: Real-time Platform Reference FOM
modelIdentification.purpose: Common Foundation Reference FOM (CF-RFOM) as defined by the SISO Reference FOM Study Group (see Simulation Interoperability Standards Organization, 'Reference FOM Study Group Final Report,' Version 1.0, March 9, 1998).
modelIdentification.applicationDomain:
Real time, platform level simulations. This FOM is based upon the following baseline documents:

1. IEEE 1278.1-1995
2. Enumeration and Bit Encoded Values for Use with Protocols for Distributed Interactive Simulation Applications, IST-CF-02-01 (commonly known as EBV 2002-1).

objectClass.name: BaseEntity
objectClass.semantics: A base class of aggregate and discrete scenaro domain participants. The BaseEntity class is characterised by being located at a particular location in space and independently movable, if capable of movement at all. It specifically excludes elements normally considered to be a component of another element. The BaseEntity class is intended to be a container for common attributes for entities of this type. Since it lacks sufficient class specific attributes that are required for simulation purposes it is not expected that any federate shall publish objects of this class. Certain simulation management federates, e.g. viewers, may subscribe to this class. Simulation federates will normally subscribe to one of the subclasses, to gain the extra information required to properly simulate the entity. (See section 6.1 of the GRIM)

attribute.name: EntityType
attribute.semantics: The category of the entity.

attribute.name: EntityIdentifier
attribute.semantics: The unique identifier for the entity instance.

attribute.name: IsPartOf
attribute.semantics: Defines if the entity if a constituent part of another entity (denoted the host entity). If the entity is a constituent part of another entity then the ParentEntityID shall be set to the EntityID of the host entity and the ParentRTIObjectID shall be set to the RTO object ID of the host entity. If the entity is not a constituent part of another entity then the ParentEntityID shall being set to 0.0.0 and the ParentRTIObjectID shall be set to the empty string.

objectClass.name: MinefieldData
objectClass.semantics: Provides information on individual mines contained within a minefield

attribute.name: GroundBurialDepthOffset
attribute.semantics: Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the ground surface. This offset can be used in conjunction with the mine orienteation to determine the actual ground burial depth of the surfaces of a mine. Ground burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meteres below the wate surface along the up vector.

attribute.name: Fusing
attribute.semantics: Specifies the primary and secondary fuse and anti-handling device for each mine.

attribute.name: MineEmplacementTime
attribute.semantics: Specifies the real-world (UTC) emplacement time of the mine.

attribute.name: MineEntityIdentifier
attribute.semantics: Specifies the mine entity identifier number. The mine ID in conjunction with the MinefieldID form the unique identifier for each mine.

attribute.name: MinefieldIdentifier
attribute.semantics: Identifies the minefield to which the mines belong

attribute.name: MineLocation
attribute.semantics: Specifies the location of the relative to the minfield location.

attribute.name: MineOrientation
attribute.semantics: Specifies the orientation of the center axis direction of fire of the mine, relative to the minefield Coordinate System. If any of the three burial depth offsets is sent in the Record , this field shall also be sent.

attribute.name: MineType
attribute.semantics: Specifies the type of each mine contained within the minefield interaction

attribute.name: NumberTripDetonationWires
attribute.semantics: Specifies the number of trip detonation wires that exist for each mine. I sub n designates the trip wire count for mine n of N.

attribute.name: NumberWireVertices
attribute.semantics: Specifies the number of vertices are in each trip wire. A set of I sub n vertex counts is given for each mine n of N, iff I sub n > 0. If I sub n is 0, the vertex count set is empty. Each non empty set of vertex counts (I sub n > 0) follows the previous non empty set. J sub i designates the vertex count of tripwire i of I sub n.

attribute.name: PaintScheme
attribute.semantics: Specifies the camouflage scheme/color of the mine.

attribute.name: Reflectance
attribute.semantics: Specifies the local dielectric difference between the mine and the surrounding soil.

attribute.name: ScalarDetectionCoefficient
attribute.semantics: Specifies the coefficient to be utilized to insure proper correlation between detctors located on different simulation platforms. In statistically based detection system applications, the detection system simulation will generally compare a random number against an internally calculated probability of detection. There are M (number of sensors) coefficients for each of the N mines. Question: all of type 1 first then all of type 2 OR all of mine 1 first then mine 2.

attribute.name: SensorTypes
attribute.semantics: In QRP mode, specifies the requesting sensor types which were specified in the minefield query. In heartbeat mode, specifies the sensor types that are bein served by the minefield.

attribute.name: SnowBurialDepthOffset
attribute.semantics: Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the snow surface. This offset can be used in conjuncition with the mine orientation to determine the actual snow baurial depth of the survaces of a mine. Snow burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meters below the snow surface along the up vector.

attribute.name: ThermalContrast
attribute.semantics: Specifies the temperature difference between the mine and the surround soil in degrees Centigrade. In the case of a buried mine, the delta temperature shall be measured between the ground surface above the mine and the surrounding ground surface temperature.

attribute.name: WaterBurialDepthOffset
attribute.semantics: Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the water surface. This offset can be used in conjunction with the mine orienteation to determine the actual water burial depth of the surfaces of a mine. Water burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meteres below the wate surface along the up vector.

attribute.name: WireVertices
attribute.semantics: Specifies the vertices in a trip wire. A set of J sub i vertices is given for each trip wire i of I sub n, iff I sub n is > 0 and J sub i > 0. If I sub n is 0 or J sub i is 0, the vertex set is empty. Each non empty set of verticies (J sub i > 0) follows the previous non empty set.

interactionClass.name: ActionRequest

parameter.semantics: The DIS entity ID of the entity or application which is the intended recipient of the interaction.

parameter.name: RequestIdentifier
parameter.semantics: The Request ID is a monotonically increasing integer identifier inserted by the Simulation Manager into all Simulation management interactions. It is used as a unique identifier to identify the latest in a series of competing requests and identifying acknowledgements.

parameter.name: ActionRequestCode
parameter.semantics: The action that the recipient(s) are requested to perform.

parameter.name: FixedDatums

interactionClass.name: MinefieldData
interactionClass.semantics: Provides information on individual mines contained within a minefield

parameter.name: GroundBurialDepthOffset
parameter.semantics: Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the ground surface. This offset can be used in conjunction with the mine orienteation to determine the actual ground burial depth of the surfaces of a mine. Ground burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meteres below the wate surface along the up vector.

parameter.name: Fusing
parameter.semantics: Specifies the primary and secondary fuse and anti-handling device for each mine.

parameter.name: MineEmplacementTime
parameter.semantics: Specifies the real-world, coordinated universal time (UTC) emplacement time of a mine.

parameter.name: MineEntityIdentifier
parameter.semantics: Specifies the mine entity identifier number. The mine identification in conjunction with the MinefieldID form the unique identifier for each mine.

parameter.name: MinefieldIdentifier
parameter.semantics: Identifies the minefield to which the mines belong

parameter.name: MineLocation
parameter.semantics: Specifies the location of the relative to the minfield location.

parameter.name: MineOrientation
parameter.semantics: Specifies the orientation of the center axis direction of fire of the mine, relative to the minefield Coordinate System. If any of the three burial depth offsets is sent in the Record , this field shall also be sent.

parameter.name: MineType
parameter.semantics: Specifies the type of each mine contained within the minefield interaction

parameter.name: NumberOfRecords
parameter.semantics: Specifies the total number of minefiled records being sent in response to a minefield Query interaction.

parameter.name: NumberTripDetonationWires
parameter.semantics: Specifies the number of trip detonation wires that exist for each mine. I sub n designates the trip wire count for mine n of N.

parameter.name: NumberWireVertices
parameter.semantics: Specifies the number of vertices are in each trip wire. A set of I sub n vertex counts is given for each mine n of N, iff I sub n > 0. If I sub n is 0, the vertex count set is empty. Each non empty set of vertex counts (I sub n > 0) follows the previous non empty set. J sub i designates the vertex count of tripwire i of I sub n.

parameter.name: PaintScheme
parameter.semantics: Specifies the camouflage scheme and color of the mine.

parameter.name: RecordSequenceNumber
parameter.semantics: Specifies the number of the current record in a sequence of minefiled records sent in response to a query interaction.

parameter.name: Reflectance
parameter.semantics: Specifies the local dielectric difference between the mine and the surrounding soil.

parameter.name: RequestIdentifier
parameter.semantics: Identifies the matching response to a request for mine information from the minefield simulation made by means of a Query interaction

parameter.name: RequestingEntityIdentifier
parameter.semantics: Identifies the matching response to a request for mine information from the associated minefield object state.

parameter.name: ScalarDetectionCoefficient
parameter.semantics: Specifies the coefficient to be utilized to insure proper correlation between detctors located on different simulation platforms. In statistically based detection system applications, the detection system simulation will generally compare a random number against an internally calculated probability of detection. There are M (number of sensors) coefficients for each of the N mines. Question: all of type 1 first then all of type 2 OR all of mine 1 first then mine 2.

parameter.name: SensorTypes
parameter.semantics: In QRP mode, specifies the requesting sensor types which were specified in the minefield query. In heartbeat mode, specifies the sensor types that are bein served by the minefield.

parameter.name: SnowBurialDepthOffset
parameter.semantics: Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the snow surface. This offset can be used in conjuncition with the mine orientation to determine the actual snow baurial depth of the survaces of a mine. Snow burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meters below the snow surface along the up vector.

parameter.name: ThermalContrast
parameter.semantics: Specifies the temperature difference between the mine and the surround soil in degrees Centigrade. In the case of a buried mine, the delta temperature shall be measured between the ground surface above the mine and the surrounding ground surface temperature.

parameter.name: WaterBurialDepthOffset
parameter.semantics: Specifies the offset of the origin of the mine coordinate system with respect to the water surface. This offset can be used in conjunction with the mine orienteation to determine the actual water burial depth of the surfaces of a mine. Water burial depth offset is specified as a positive measurement in meteres below the wate surface along the up vector.

parameter.name: WireVertices
parameter.semantics: Specifies the vertices in a trip wire. A set of J sub i vertices is given for each trip wire i of I sub n, iff I sub n is > 0 and J sub i > 0. If I sub n is 0 or J sub i is 0, the vertex set is empty. Each non empty set of verticies (J sub i > 0) follows the previous non empty set.

parameter.semantics: The ID of the object being fired at (if any).

parameter.name: WarheadType
parameter.semantics: The type of warhead fitted to the munition being fired.

interactionClass.name: TransferControl
interactionClass.semantics: A Simulation Management (SIMAN) interaction, sent to initiate the transfer of control of an entity.

parameter.name: OriginatingEntity
parameter.semantics: The DIS entity ID of the entity or application sending the interaction.

parameter.name: ReceivingEntity
parameter.semantics: The DIS entity ID of the entity or application which is the intended recipient of the interaction.

parameter.name: RequestIdentifier
parameter.semantics: The Request ID is a monotonically increasing integer identifier inserted by the Simulation Manager into all Simulation management interactions. It is used as a unique identifier to identify the latest in a series of competing requests and identifying acknowledgements.

parameter.name: TransferType
parameter.semantics: The type of transfer to be performed.

parameter.name: TransferEntity
parameter.semantics: The ID of the object to be transferred.

parameter.name: RecordSetData
parameter.semantics: Specifies the information, in record format, to be set by the receiving entity.

simpleData.name: DeflectionAngle
simpleData.semantics: SEES Vectoring Nozzle System Data deflection angle.

simpleData.name: ElectricField
simpleData.semantics: Scalar magintude of an electric field.

enumeratedData.name: OMT13boolean
enumeratedData.semantics: Standard boolean type used for 8-bit compatibility

enumeratedData.name: ParameterTypeEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: Kind of parameter value in variant record.

enumeratedData.name: StationEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: Station on host of an attached part.

arrayData.name: OMT13string
arrayData.semantics: A null terminated string with no length field.

fixedRecordData.name: EventIdentifierStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: Uniquely identifies an event from an object instance.

field.name: EventCount
field.semantics: EventCount shall be set to one for each exercise and incremented by one for each fire event, collision event, or electromagnetic mission event. In the case where all possible values are exhausted, the numbers may be reused beginning again at one.

field.name: IssuingObjectIdentifier
field.semantics: The object which issued the event.

fixedRecordData.name: EntityTypeStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: This record shall specify the kind of entity, the country of design, the domain, the specific identification of the entity, and any extra information necessary for describing the entity. Fields not used shall contain the value zero. Refer to section 4 of EBV-DOC.

field.name: EntityKind
field.semantics: This field shall identify the kind of entity described by the Entity Type record.

field.name: Domain
field.semantics: This field shall specify the domain in which the entity operates (e.g., subsurface, surface, land) except for munition entities. For munition entities this field shall specify the domain of the target (for example, the munition might be a surface-to-air, so the domain would be anti-air).

field.name: CountryCode
field.semantics: This field shall specify the country to which the design of the entity is attributed.

field.name: Category
field.semantics: This field shall specify the main category that describes the entity.

field.name: Subcategory
field.semantics: This field shall specify a particular subcategory to which an entity belongs based on the Category field.

field.name: Specific
field.semantics: This field shall specify specific information about an entity based on the Subcategory field.

field.name: Extra
field.semantics: This field shall specify extra information required to describe a particular entity.

field.name: EntityNumber
field.semantics: Identifies entities within the federate specified by FederateIdentifier. EntityNumbers must be unique within each federate given by FederateIdentifier. An EntityNumber is valid for the duration of the exercise; however, EntityNumbers may be reused when all possible numbers have been exhausted. No entity shall have an EntityNumber of NO_ENTITY, ALL_ENTITIES, or RQST_ASSIGN_ID (see IEEE 1278). The EntityNumber need not be registered or retained for future exercises. An EntityNumber equal to zero with a valid FederateIdentifier shall address a simulation application. An EntityNumber equal to ALL_ENTITIES shall mean all entities within the federate specified by FederateIdentifier.

field.name: HostEntityIdentifier
field.semantics: The identifier of the entity of which this entity is a constituent part

field.name: HostRTIObjectIdentifier
field.semantics: The RTI object identifier of the entity of which this entity is a constituent part

field.name: Relationship
field.semantics: The relationship of the constituent part entity to its host entity

field.name: NamedLocation
field.semantics: The discrete positional relationship of the constituent part entity with respect to its host entity

fixedRecordData.name: AggregateMarkingStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: This record shall specify the character set used in the marking and the string of characters to be interpreted for display.

fixedRecordData.name: MarkingStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: Specifies the character set used in the marking and the string of characters to be interpreted for display.

fixedRecordData.name: WorldLocationStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: Location of the origin of the entity's coordinate system shall be specified by a set of three coordinates: X, Y, and Z. The shape of the earth shall be specified using DMA TR 8350.2, 1987. The origin of the world coordinate system shall be the centroid of the earth, with the X-axis passing through the prime meridian at the equator, the Y-axis passing through 90 degrees east longitude at the equator, and the Z-axis passing through the north pole. These coordinates shall represent meters from the centroid of the earth.

field.name: XAcceleration
field.semantics: Acceleration component along the X axis

field.name: YAcceleration
field.semantics: Acceleration component along the Y axis

field.name: ZAcceleration
field.semantics: Acceleration component along the Z axis

fixedRecordData.name: OrientationStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: A set of three angles used to describe the orientation of an entity as a set of three successive rotations about three different orthogonal axes (x, y, and z). These angles specify the successive rotations needed to transform from the world coordinate system to the entity coordinate system. The positive direction of rotation about an axis is defined by the right-hand rule.

field.name: Psi
field.semantics: Rotation around z-axis, applied first. Ranges from -pi to +pi.

field.name: Theta
field.semantics: Rotation around y-axis, applied second. Ranges from -pi to +pi.

field.name: Phi
field.semantics: Rotation around x-axis, applied third. Ranges from -pi/2 to +pi/2.

fixedRecordData.name: FederateIdentifierStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: Specifies federates by their site and application. Unlike an object instance name used by an RTI, this record identifies sites and as well as federates, can specify multiple federates or simply sites alone.

field.name: SiteID
field.semantics: Uniquely identifies a single site. No individual site shall be assigned a SiteID containing NO_SITE or ALL_SITES. A SiteID equal to ALL_SITES shall mean all sites; this may be used to initialize or start all sites. The mechanism by which SiteID numbers are assigned is outside the scope of this standard.

field.name: ApplicationID
field.semantics: Uniquely identifies a single federate within the site given by SiteID. No simulation application shall be assigned an ApplicationID containing NO_APPLIC or ALL_APPLIC. An ApplicationID equal to ALL_APPLIC shall mean all applications; this may be used to start all applications within a site. One or more simulation applications may reside in a single host computer. The mechanism by which ApplicationID numbers are assigned is outside the scope of this standard.

field.name: StreamTag
field.semantics: Identifier for the audio stream. This must be globally unique.

field.name: EncodingType
field.semantics: The type of encoding used for the audio data

field.name: SampleRate
field.semantics: The number of samples per second in the signal data.

field.name: DataLength
field.semantics: The length of the signal data.

field.name: Hours
field.semantics: The number of hours since 0000 hours, January 1, 1970 UTC.

field.name: TimePastTheHour
field.semantics: The time past the hour indicated in the Hours field.

fixedRecordData.name: AttributePairStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: This record contains a handle-value pair, which specifies a value for a particular simulation parameter.

field.name: Handle
field.semantics: A handle which identifies a simulation parameter.

field.name: Value
field.semantics: Value format must be determined from the corresponding value of Handle.

fixedRecordData.name: ArticulatedParameterStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: The specification of articulation parameters for movable parts and attached parts of an entity shall be represented by an Articulation Parameter record. This record shall specify whether or not a change has occurred, the part identification of the articulated part to which it is attached, and the type and value of each parameter (see annex A of IEEE 1278.1-1995 for further explanation, figures, and examples).

field.name: ChangeIndicator
field.semantics: This field shall indicate the change of any parameter for any articulated part. This field shall be set to zero for each exercise and sequentially incremented by one for each change in articulation parameters. In the case where all possible values are exhausted, the numbers shall be reused beginning at zero.

field.name: PartAttachedTo
field.semantics: This field shall specify the identification of the articulated part to which this articulation parameter is attached. This field shall contain the value zero if the articulated part is attached directly to the entity.

field.name: ParameterValue
field.semantics: This field shall specify the parameter value.

field.name: PowerSetting
field.semantics: The power setting of the propulsion system, after any response lags have been incorporated

field.name: HorizontalDeflectionAngle
field.semantics: The nozzle deflection angle in the horizontal body axis of the entity

field.name: VerticalDeflectionAngle
field.semantics: The nozzle deflection angle in the vertical body axis of the entity

field.name: ERP
field.semantics: The average peak radiated power of the emission

field.name: Frequency
field.semantics: The center frequency of the emission

field.name: PgRF
field.semantics: When applied to originators, this field shall specify the number of interrogations per second emitted. This field shall be set to zero when applied to a responder (i.e. transponder) systems

field.name: PulseWidth
field.semantics: The duration of the fundamental pulse of which the interrogation or reply is composed

field.name: BurstLength
field.semantics: The number of emissions generated in a single burst. This field shall contain zero for continuously emitting systems and shall contain the value 1 for responders.

field.name: ApplicableModes
field.semantics: Specifies the modes to which the fundamental paremeter data applies

field.name: CurrentShaftRate
field.semantics: The current shaft speed. A positive shaft speed indicates that the shaft is rotating in a clockwise direction (when viewed from the stern to bow), and a negative shaft speed indicates an anti-clockwise direction.

field.name: OrderedShaftRate
field.semantics: The ordered shaft speed. If the ordered shaft speed is different from the current shaft speed then the shaft will accelerate or decelerate at the shaft rate of change. A positive shaft speed indicates that the shaft is rotating in a clockwise direction (when viewed from the stern to bow), and a negative shaft speed indicates an anti-clockwise direction.

field.name: ShaftRateOfChange
field.semantics: The rate of change of shaft speed. The shaft will change its rotational speed at this rate if the current shaft speed differs from the ordered shaft rate.

field.name: Quantity
field.semantics: The number of units of the supply type. The unit measure depends on the supply type and shall use the SI units of measurement used for such supplies.

fixedRecordData.name: AngularVelocityVectorStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: This record shall specify the rate at which an entity's orientation is changing. The angular velocity shall be measured about each of the entity's own coordinate axes. The positive direction of the angular velocity is defined by the right-hand rule.

fixedRecordData.name: ArticulatedPartsStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: A single parameter of an articulated part.

field.name: Class
field.semantics: The type class uniquely identifies a particular articulated part on a given entity type.

field.name: TypeMetric
field.semantics: The type metric uniquely identifies the transformation to be applied to the articulated part.

field.name: Value
field.semantics: Interpretation of Value depends on value of TypeMetric field.

fixedRecordData.name: AttachedPartsStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: The AttachedPartsStruct represents removable parts that may be attached to an entity. Examples of such attached parts include missiles and other external stores on an aircraft.

field.name: Station
field.semantics: Station on host entity where the part is attached.

fixedRecordData.name: BeamAntennaStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: This record specifies the direction, pattern, and polarization of radiation from a radio transmitter's antenna. The radiation pattern produced by the antenna is defined with respect to a beam coordinate system. The beam coordinate system is a right-handed Cartesian coordinate system with the center of the beam along the x-axis of the system.

field.name: Orientation
field.semantics: This field shall specify the rotation that transforms the reference coordinate system into the beam coordinate system. Either world coordinates or entity coordinates may be used as the reference coordinate system. The reference coordinate system in use shall be specified by the ReferenceSystem field.

field.name: AzimuthBeamwidth
field.semantics: This field shall specify the full width of the beam to the -3 dB power density points in the x-y plane of the beam coordinate system.

field.name: ElevationBeamwidth
field.semantics: This field shall specify the full width of the beam to the -3 dB power density points in the x-y plane of the beam coordinate system.

field.name: ReferenceSystem
field.semantics: Reference coordinate system with respect to which beam direction is specified. The value of this field shall not change over the duration of an exercise. Different radios in the same exercise may use different reference systems. The world coordinate system is the preferred reference system for training applications. The entity coordinate system should only be used where highly directional antennas must be precisely modeled. Use of the entity coordinates for a reference system requires the receipt of entity coordinate updates by radio simulation applications and may adversely affect their performance. Support for an entity coordinate reference system is an optional part of this standard.

field.name: Ez
field.semantics: Magnitude of the Z-component (in beam coordinates) of the Electrical field at some arbitrary single point in the mainbeam and in the far field of the antenna

field.name: Ex
field.semantics: Magnitude of the X-component (in beam coordinates) of the Electrical field at some arbitrary single point in the mainbeam and in the far field of the antenna

field.name: Phase
field.semantics: This field shall specify the phase angle between EZ and EX in radians. If fully omni-directional antenna is modeled using beam pattern type one, the omni-directional antenna shall be represented by beam direction Euler angles [psi(y), theta(q), and phi(f)] of zero, an azimuth beamwidth of 2pi, and an elevation beamwidth of pi.

field.name: Nature
field.semantics: The nature or purpose for the joining of theconstituent part entity to the host entity

field.name: Position
field.semantics: The position of the constituent part entity with respect to the host entity

field.name: StationNumber
field.semantics: The number of the particular station at which the constituent part is attached

field.name: StationName-A-Alternatives
field.semantics: The name of the station, within the host entity, where the constituent part entity is located

field.name: Range
field.semantics: The range from the specified location

field.name: Bearing
field.semantics: The bearing relative to the specified location

variantRecordData.name: ParameterValueStruct
variantRecordData.semantics: ParameterValueStruct can be used in two ways. The first is to represent articulated parts of an entity. The second is to represent attached parts.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_1
note.semantics: Value is integer percent from 1 to 100

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_2
note.semantics: The units for the MarkingData are specified by the value of the MarkingEncodingType.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_3
note.semantics:
The AttributeChangeResult interaction should be sent in response to an AttributeChangeRequest interaction by any object that is mentioned in the associated object list. The AttributeChangeResult parameter should indicate the success or failure of the object to implement the requested changes. If the object can implement the changes then the AttributeChangeResult parameter should be set to successful and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty.

If the object cannot immediately comply with the request, but is likely to be able to comply in the future then the AttributeChangeRequest parameter shall be set to pending and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty. When the object complies with the request (or fails to implement the request) then another AttributeChangeResult interaction shall be sent informing the initiating federate of the result of the request.

If the object cannot comply with the request then the AttributeChangeResult parameter shall indicate the reason why the object cannot comply with the request, The AttributeValueSet shall contain the attributes which have been not been set and the current values of those attributes.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_4
note.semantics: This is the unique ObjectName associated with each object instance. The user can define the name to be used in the registerObjectInstance RTI call. If user does not define the name then the RTI will generate a unique name for the object. RTI generated names may be fairly long, so federations wishing to conserve bandwidth may wish to implement their own object naming scheme. \r\n\r\nThe ObjectName is provided by the RTI in the discoverObjectInstance call. The user can also obtain the ObjectName for a particular object instance using the getObjectInstanceName call.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_5
note.semantics: Currently the entity type record is a variant record as in DIS (the meaning of the enumerations in each field depends on the enumerations in the fields preceding it). In the future it is intended to flatten the structure so that there is a single set of enumerations for each field. This may be achieved by offsetting the start of each block of enumerations, using different offsets for each block.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_6
note.semantics: The current OMT standard does not allow the definition of variant records in complex data types, i.e. where a field may be present or absent according to the state of another variable (although the RTI does not disallow this, since the application is responsible for the data marshalling of complex data types). The RPR-FOM uses the convention that a cardinality of 0-1 denotes a variant record field.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_7
note.semantics:
The contents of the AntennaPatternStruct complex datatype depends on the value of the AntennaPatternType attribute as follows:

Values: 'Other' or 'OmniDirectional'
 Structure is empty

Value: 'Beam'
 Structure contains 1 'BeamAntenna' field and 0 SphericalHarmonicAntenna' fields

Value: 'SphericalHarmonic'
 Structure contains 0 'BeamAntenna' field and 1 SphericalHarmonicAntenna' fields

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_8
note.semantics: This is an 8-bit enumeration

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_9
note.semantics: This is a 16-bit enumeration

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_10
note.semantics: This is a 32-bit enumeration

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_11
note.semantics: This structure is taken directly from the IEEE 1278.1-1995 (DIS) definition of the Spherical Harmonic Antenna Pattern record (section 5.2.4.3). It does not comply with the DIS field alignment rules (which is an error in the DIS standard). Therefore some federates may not be able to process this structure directly, but must copy the contents a field at a time to an equivalent structure that does comply with the DIS field alignment rules.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_12
note.semantics: The Acknowledge interaction is issued in response to the CreateEntity, RemoveEntity, StartResume, and StopFreeze interactions. See (DIS 4.4.5.4.5 Acknowledge PDU) and (DIS 5.4.6.5 Acknowledge PDU).

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_13
note.semantics: This is a timestamp record (see DIS 5.2.31)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_14
note.semantics: Each element i indicates whether the portion of the segment beginning at the segment origin + (i*Breach Length) and extending i* Breach Length meters is breached or not.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_15
note.semantics: The AcknowledgeR interaction is issued in response to the CreateEntityR, RemoveEntityR, StartResumeR, and StopFreezeR interactions. See (DIS 4.4.11.3.5 Acknowledge-R PDU) and (DIS 5.3.12.5 Acknowledge-R PDU).

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_16
note.semantics: See DIS 4.5.11 for a description of the acknowledgement protocols (called reliability services in that document).

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_17
note.semantics: If the EntityNumber field is set to RQST_ASSIGN_ID (hex FFFE) then the receiving application should assign the entity number. Entity identifications shall be in accordance with DIS 5.2.14.2.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_18
note.semantics: The Request ID is a monotonically increasing integer identifier inserted by the Simulation Manager into all Simulation management interactions. It is used as a unique identifier to identify the latest in a series of competing requests and identifying acknowledgements.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_19
note.semantics: This field matches this response with the specific ActionRequest interaction sent by the simulation manager.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_20
note.semantics: This field matches this response with the specific SetData or DataQuery interaction sent by the simulation manager.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_21
note.semantics: This field matches this response with the specific RemoveObject interaction sent by the simulation manager.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_22
note.semantics: If there is no object instance associated with the attribute, then this should be set to the empty string (no characters).

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_23
note.semantics: Only one of the varient record types is included in each intercom parameter structure. The particular structure included is determined by the value of the RecordType field

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_24
note.semantics: This must reference a valid Object instance.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_25
note.semantics: Federates shall send the time at which the data is valid in the user defined tag with every attribute values update and interaction. The time shall be in the first 8 bytes (octets) of the user defined tag, using the DIS timestamp field format (see section 5.2.31 of IEEE 1278.1-1995) converted into hexadecimal ASCII character representation (0-9 and A-F). The ordering of the characters shall be in accordance with section 5.1.1 of IEEE 1278.1-1995, that is most significant octet first, with the most significant bits first (i.e. the character for bits 4-7 precedes the character for bits 0-3).\r\n\r\nAll federates shall transmit this field, even if they do not use it themselves, so that other federates can use its value to compensate for network transport delays.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_26
note.semantics: The EventIdentifier attribute is used to link together updates arising from a common event. For example an emitter function change can be linked to a frequency change in one of its associated emitter beams, by using the same event ID in the attribute updates to the appropriate EmitterSystem and EmitterBeam classes.\r\n\r\nIt is important to note that in order that the EventIdentifier is delivered in the same reflect attribute values call in the receiving federates as the associated attributes, then all the attributes, including the EventIdentifier, must share the same transport type.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_27
note.semantics: The federate should change the value of the EventIdentifier when associating changes between two or more emitter beams and/or emitter systems. It is not necessary to update the EventIdentifier field with every attribute update if the change is not associated with changes in other instances of other classes.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_28
note.semantics: Warning - this data type corresponds with the definition of attribute handles in the current RTI specification (v1.3). The RTI specification does not guarantee that the attribute handle will continue to use this data type in future versions of the standard.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_29
note.semantics: All fields in the entity type struct are enumerations. The values for the individual fields are defined in section for of 'Enumeration and Bit-Encoded Values for use with IEEE 1278.1-1995' (EBV-DOC). The values used in this structure should comply with the requirements specified in section 5.2.16 of IEEE 1278.1-1995 (for platform and environmental entities) and section 5.2.39 of IEEE 1278.1A-1998 (for aggregate entities).

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_30
note.semantics:
The emitter names have been generated from the names in the enumeration document (EBV-DOC) according to the following rules:

a) The emitter name is the National Nomenclature name if there is one. If not then the emitter name is the NATO Reporting Name, if there is one. If not then then the emitter name is the Commercial Designation.
b) All spaces have been replaced by underscores.
c) If emitter name starts with a digit, then prepend 'Emitter_'.
d) The round barck characters, '(' and ')' have been replaced with angle brackets, '<' and '>' respectively.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_31
note.semantics: The object IDs in this structure shall refer to EmitterBeam objects (or subclasses of EmitterBeam)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_32
note.semantics: The object IDs in this structure shall refer to PhysicalEntity objects (or subclasses of PhysicalEntity)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_33
note.semantics:
The contents of the ParameterValueStruct complex datatype depends on the value of the ParameterType attribute as follows:

Values: 'ArticulatedPart'
 Structure contains 1 'ArticulatedParts' field and 0 'AttachedParts' fields

Value: 'AttachedPart'
 Structure contains 0 'ArticulatedParts' field and 1 'AttachedParts' fields

The active field is located immediately after the ParameterType field (i.e. both the ArticulatedParts field and AttachedParts field start at an offset of 4 bytes from the start of the ParameterValueStruct).

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_34
note.semantics: All the fields in the radio type struct are enumerations. The values for the individual fields (that do not use enumeration datatypes from within the RPR FOM) are defined in section for of 'Enumeration and Bit-Encoded Values for use with IEEE 1278.1-1995' (EBV-DOC). The values used in this structure should comply with the requirements specified in section 5.2.16 of IEEE 1278.1-1995.

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_35
note.semantics: This attribute is updated if the current value differs from the previously updated value by more than the value specified by the symbolic name (see section 5.1.4 of IEE 1278.1-1995 for the actual values of the symbolic names)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_36
note.semantics: See section 5.1.4 of IEEE 1278.1-1995 for the values of the symbolic name

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_37
note.semantics: This condition is TRUE when TSPI_Change is TRUE and the actual accleration differs from the last transmitted acceleration by more than a threshold value in any direction. The default threshold shall be DRA_ACCEL_EPSILON_DFLT (see note 44)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_38
note.semantics:
The TSPI_Change condition shall be evaluated as follows:

The owner of a base entity object shall maintain two state models of the object in support of the dead reckoning process. One model shall be the internal model used by the simulation application to represent that object. The other shall be a dead reckoning model of the object. Certain thresholds shall be established as criteria for determining if the object's actual TSPI data has varied by an allowable amount from the dead reckoned TSPI data.

TSPI_Change is TRUE when either:-
a) the objects actual position differs from the dead reckoned position by more than DRA_POS_THRSH_DFLT 
b) the objects actual orientation differs from the dead reckoned orientation by more than DRA_ORIENT_THRSH_DFLT 

See section 5.1.4 of IEEE 1278.1-1995 for the value of these symbolic constants

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_39
note.semantics: This condition is TRUE when TSPI_Change is TRUE and the actual angular velocity differs from the last transmitted angular velocity by more than a threshold value in any direction. The default threshold shall be DRA_ANG_VEL_EPSILON_DFLT (see note 44)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_40
note.semantics: This condition is TRUE when TSPI_Change is TRUE and the actual orientation differs from the last transmitted orientation by more than a threshold value in any orientation. The default threshold shall be DRA_ORIENT_EPSILON_DFLT (see note 44)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_41
note.semantics: This condition is TRUE when TSPI_Change is TRUE and the actual position differs from the last transmitted positition by more than a threshold value in any direction. The default threshold shall be DRA_POS_EPSILSON_DFLT (see note 44)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_42
note.semantics: This condition is TRUE when TSPI_Change is TRUE and the actual velocity differs from the last transmitted velocity by more than a threshold value in any direction. The default threshold shall be DRA_VEL_EPSILON_DFLT (see note 44)

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_43
note.semantics:
The values of the default update conditions is as follows:-

DRA_POS_EPSILON_DFLT 0.001 m
DRA_ORIENT_EPSILON_DFLT 0.00001 radians
DRA_VEL_EPSILON_DFLT 0.001 m/s
DRA_ACCEL_EPSILON_DFLT 0.001 m/s/s
DRA_ANG_VEL_EPSILON_DFLT 0.00001 radians/s

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_44
note.semantics: The value of DS_WAVELENGTH shall be 0.0000001 microns

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_45
note.semantics: The DatumLength equals the length in bits of the DatumValue only. The total size of a VariableDatumStruct record must account for the padding length

note.label: real-time_platform_reference_fom_46
note.semantics: There is no data associated with the uniform geometry complex data type. However, to correctly align fields within the EnvironmentRecStruct complex data type all environmental record data types (including this data type) must have a size which is a multiple of 64 bits. Hence 64 bits of padding are included in this record.

note.semantics:
The AttributeChangeResultR interaction should be sent in response to an AttributeChangeRequestR interaction by any object that is mentioned in the associated object list. The AttributeChangeResult parameter should indicate the success or failure of the object to implement the requested changes. If the object can implement the changes then the AttributeChangeResult parameter should be set to successful and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty.

If the object cannot immediately comply with the request, but is likely to be able to comply in the future then the AttributeChangeRequest parameter shall be set to pending and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty. When the object complies with the request (or fails to implement the request) then another AttributeChangeResultR interaction shall be sent informing the initiating federate of the result of the request.

If the object cannot comply with the request then the AttributeChangeResult parameter shall indicate the reason why the object cannot comply with the request, The AttributeValueSet shall contain the attributes which have been not been set and the current values of those attributes.
